<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<xmi:XMI xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1">
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ProcessDescription xmi:id="-pAHeZaP9CLqIpxrDIYoRKA" name="se_analysis_design_discipline,_9MQf0VVmEdq-S-2DETo4XA" guid="-pAHeZaP9CLqIpxrDIYoRKA">
    <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    In Inception, the concern is to establish feasibility and explore alternatives if necessary in &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/capabilitypatterns/synthesize_system_architecture_B65AF7C1.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_f-muUVVwEdqgIdhbAiG50A&quot;>Activity: Synthesize System Architecture&lt;/a>. Given the nature of the systems under&#xD;
    development with this approach—often large, complex and with a mix of hardware, software, and people—it is unlikely&#xD;
    that this&amp;nbsp;activity will be omitted. The behavior of the tentative architecture is examined in &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/capabilitypatterns/analyze_system_behavior_38A5919C.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_5tCbYFVwEdqgIdhbAiG50A&quot;>Activity: Analyze System Behavior&lt;/a>, and the required behavior of the constituent&#xD;
    subsystems begins to emerge.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    During Elaboration, the System Architecture is established, over one or more iterations, in &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/capabilitypatterns/define_candidate_system_architecture_38D95EDC.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_tWbEAFVwEdqgIdhbAiG50A&quot;>Activity: Define Candidate System Architecture&lt;/a>, and the required behavior of the&#xD;
    constituent subsystems is established. As discoveries are made or changes required, in any phase, the system&#xD;
    architecture is refined in &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/capabilitypatterns/refine_system_architecture_ED478575.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_1ln6EFVwEdqgIdhbAiG50A&quot;>Activity: Refine System Architecture&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:ProcessDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription xmi:id="-GBw8fDUWkl0Xwd-5F_5xNQ" name="synthesize_system_architecture,_f-muUVVwEdqgIdhbAiG50A" guid="-GBw8fDUWkl0Xwd-5F_5xNQ">
    <usageGuidance>This work takes place during Inception, and so should be limited to one or two iterations. The purpose is to gain knowledge&#xD;
and determine feasibility, not to construct the system during this activity. &lt;br /></usageGuidance>
    <howtoStaff>This activity is best carried out by a small team (playing the role of &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/roles/rup_system_architect,{A83E9C0E-3BBD-4D5A-902F-3B82F21975E3}.html&quot; guid=&quot;{A83E9C0E-3BBD-4D5A-902F-3B82F21975E3}&quot;>System Architect&lt;/a>, and usually guided by one or two individuals who have
deep experience in architecting systems in the relevant domain) staffed by cross-functional team members. Issues that are
typically architecturally important include performance, scaling, distribution, or other specialty engineering
requirements. Significant architectural constraints might also flow from physical and environmental requirements. The team
should also include members with domain experience who can identify key abstractions. The team should also have experience
with model organization and layering. From these inputs, the team must be able to synthesize a model, or even a prototype,
of a solution.</howtoStaff>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription xmi:id="-v9EhsBNGLdz5E8RKFelw2w" name="define_candidate_system_architecture,_tWbEAFVwEdqgIdhbAiG50A" guid="-v9EhsBNGLdz5E8RKFelw2w">
    <usageGuidance>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The work is best done in several sessions, perhaps performed over a few days (or weeks and months for very large&#xD;
    systems), with iteration over &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/tasks/architectural_analysis_30D2538.html&quot; guid=&quot;{B7FABC7A-42FA-4DC7-A1F4-C4F5DB6F673F}&quot;>System&#xD;
    Architectural Analysis&lt;/a> and&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/tasks/se_operation_analysis_6C6BED14.html&quot; guid=&quot;_GMjFYOQ5Edm1mN374l9mbg&quot;>System Operation&#xD;
    Analysis&lt;/a>. Perform an initial pass at the architecture in System Architectural Analysis, then choose architecturally&#xD;
    significant system use cases, performing System&amp;nbsp;Operation Analysis on each one. After (or as) each use case is&#xD;
    analyzed, update the architecture as needed to reflect adaptations required to accommodate new behavior of the system&#xD;
    and to address potential architectural problems which are identified.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Where the architecture already exists (either from a prior project or iteration), change requests might need to be&#xD;
    created to change the architecture to account for the new behavior the system must support. These changes can be to any&#xD;
    artifact in the process, depending on the scope of the change.&#xD;
&lt;/p></usageGuidance>
    <purpose>The purpose of this&amp;nbsp;activity is to: &#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create the outlines of the architecture of the system: &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Define an initial set of architecturally significant elements (subsystems, processes and localities), for&#xD;
                analysis.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Identify collaborations (of subsystems) that will realize architecturally significant system use cases,&#xD;
                capture these (in outline) in the System Analysis Model, and decide the System Use-Case Realizations and/or&#xD;
                System Operation Realizations&amp;nbsp;to be further detailed in the current iteration.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Produce preliminary Subsystem Vision artifacts.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Capture significant decisions and rationale in System Architecture Document.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Update the System Use-Case Realizations and/or System Operation Realizations&amp;nbsp;with subsystem interactions.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Produce preliminary Subsystem Supplementary Requirements artifacts.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
    <howtoStaff>&lt;p>
    As with the early architectural synthesis work, this activity&amp;nbsp;is best carried out by a small team (playing the
    roles of &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/roles/rup_system_architect,{A83E9C0E-3BBD-4D5A-902F-3B82F21975E3}.html&quot; guid=&quot;{A83E9C0E-3BBD-4D5A-902F-3B82F21975E3}&quot;>System Architect&lt;/a> and &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/roles/rup_system_designer,{17D1CF2F-DA3E-4EC0-AB76-C8B47343183B}.html&quot; guid=&quot;{17D1CF2F-DA3E-4EC0-AB76-C8B47343183B}&quot;>System Designer&lt;/a>, and usually guided by one or two individuals who
    have deep experience in architecting systems in the relevant domain) staffed by cross-functional team members. Issues
    that are typically architecturally important include performance, scaling, distribution or other specialty engineering
    requirements. Significant architectural constraints might also flow from physical and environmental requirements. The
    team should also include members with domain experience who can identify key abstractions. The team should also have
    experience with model organization and layering.
&lt;/p></howtoStaff>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription xmi:id="-7iejRD6AFQnh0hMX6Kisug" name="refine_system_architecture,_1ln6EFVwEdqgIdhbAiG50A" guid="-7iejRD6AFQnh0hMX6Kisug">
    <usageGuidance>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This&amp;nbsp;activity allows the System Architect to revisit the structural, dynamic, and physical aspects of the system&#xD;
    architecture and rework and refine them as needed to accommodate change.&#xD;
&lt;/p></usageGuidance>
    <purpose>The purpose of this activity is to: &#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Maintain the consistency and integrity of the system architecture, ensuring that: &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                New design elements identified for the current iteration are integrated with pre-existing design elements.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Maximal re-use of available components and design elements is achieved as early as possible in the design&#xD;
                effort.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Accommodate changes arising from new or changed requirements or discoveries made during design work.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
    <howtoStaff>&lt;p>
    As with earlier architectural work, this activity is&amp;nbsp;best carried out by a small team (playing the role of&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/roles/rup_system_architect,{A83E9C0E-3BBD-4D5A-902F-3B82F21975E3}.html&quot; guid=&quot;{A83E9C0E-3BBD-4D5A-902F-3B82F21975E3}&quot;>System Architect&lt;/a>, usually guided by one or two individuals who have
    deep experience in architecting systems in the relevant domain) staffed by cross-functional team members. Issues that
    are typically architecturally important include performance, scaling, distribution, or other specialty engineering
    requirements. Significant architectural constraints might also flow from physical and environmental requirements. The
    team should also include members with domain experience who can identify key abstractions. The team should also have
    experience with model organization and layering.
&lt;/p></howtoStaff>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription xmi:id="-Q0391meCthh5id2eGVgXgw" name="analyze_system_behavior,_5tCbYFVwEdqgIdhbAiG50A" guid="-Q0391meCthh5id2eGVgXgw">
    <usageGuidance>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The driving&amp;nbsp;task in this&amp;nbsp;activity is&amp;nbsp;System Operation&amp;nbsp;Design, with the System Architect ensuring&#xD;
    the design maintains the architectural vision, while still accommodating change and feedback as design discoveries are&#xD;
    made. The System Designer delivers updated artifacts to the System Architect to allow for sanctioned Structural,&#xD;
    Process and Deployment model changes, and the System Architect refines these as necessary. Pragmatically, the way this&#xD;
    might work is that the team does system&amp;nbsp;operation design, reviews the results from an Architectural viewpoint,&#xD;
    then iterates back through system&amp;nbsp;operation design, until comfortable with the result (that is, the result meets&#xD;
    functional and non-functional requirements and satisfies architectural constraints).&#xD;
&lt;/p></usageGuidance>
    <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of this&amp;nbsp;activity is to:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Refine the preliminary subsystem interactions into &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_system_operation_realization_C5CAA59A.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_4F_bcFFGEdqQ1bHkhNnYIg&quot;>System Operation Realizations&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;and /or &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_sytem_use_case_realization_A42D6675.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{07429BA9-425C-43A4-9D33-8319FF1EEEC8}&quot;>System Use-Case Realizations&lt;/a> in the &lt;a&#xD;
        class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_system_design_model_FF4023F1.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{96746B25-06FC-4780-847E-B538C06162DB}&quot;>System Design Model&lt;/a>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Aggregate similar subsystem interactions into subsystem use cases and construct the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_subsystem_usecase_model_9C336055.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{124F1EA8-21EC-45C2-A25B-A8DCF1309FE4}&quot;>Subsystem Use-Case Model&lt;/a>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Refine the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_system_analysis_model_D73BECB2.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{CB35D940-20DA-446A-B262-C614C7753D12}&quot;>System Analysis Model&lt;/a> and &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_system_design_model_FF4023F1.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{96746B25-06FC-4780-847E-B538C06162DB}&quot;>System Design Model&lt;/a> (in terms of subsystems and their&#xD;
        relationships) and update the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_subsystem_vision_AE7C87FE.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{892CEA8C-66C5-468C-8188-F739B3954B90}&quot;>Subsystem Vision&lt;/a> and the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_subsystem_supplementary_specification_911D5D8E.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{C9B8F699-A008-4A3E-8B4D-CE829D595E5D}&quot;>Subsystem Supplementary Requirements&lt;/a> artifacts, based on work&#xD;
        done on subsystem interactions, and changes in environment, subsystem non-functional requirements, and the&#xD;
        subsystem vision.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Refine the Process Model at the system level, based on changes to the system structure (decomposition into&#xD;
        subsystems) and the system's environment.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create locality interactions in the form of sequence or collaboration diagrams (in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/workproducts/rup_system_deployment_model_C12856E8.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{F3EF5651-065C-478F-81CC-D55D90FF0CBC}&quot;>System Deployment Model&lt;/a>) using the Locality Model (Conceptual&#xD;
        level of System Deployment Model), and the sorted set of subsystem services.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Refine the Locality Model into a Descriptor Level Model and then to an implementation level, through analysis of&#xD;
        the localities, their characteristics and hosted subsystem services.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Update the appropriate viewpoints in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/guidances/templates/system_architecture_document_5B807A1F.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;1.3184560012908812E-305&quot;>System Architecture Document&lt;/a> with any architecturally significant changes.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
    <howtoStaff>&lt;p>
    The &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/tasks/se_operation_design,_Gb4P8OQ7Edm1mN374l9mbg.html&quot; guid=&quot;_Gb4P8OQ7Edm1mN374l9mbg&quot;>System Operation Design&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;task is performed by the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/roles/rup_system_designer,{17D1CF2F-DA3E-4EC0-AB76-C8B47343183B}.html&quot; guid=&quot;{17D1CF2F-DA3E-4EC0-AB76-C8B47343183B}&quot;>System Designer&lt;/a> role, which in this&amp;nbsp;activity requires a
    combination of analysis and synthesis skills, in first describing subsystem interactions in detail and then
    synthesizing these interactions into descriptions of required subsystem behavior in use cases. The results of this work
    are reviewed by the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/roles/rup_system_architect,{A83E9C0E-3BBD-4D5A-902F-3B82F21975E3}.html&quot; guid=&quot;{A83E9C0E-3BBD-4D5A-902F-3B82F21975E3}&quot;>System Architect&lt;/a> and any needed adjustments and refinements are made
    with the broad system architectural picture and issues in mind. This work is a continuation of that begun in &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../systems.rup_se/capabilitypatterns/define_candidate_system_architecture,_tWbEAFVwEdqgIdhbAiG50A.html&quot; guid=&quot;_tWbEAFVwEdqgIdhbAiG50A&quot;>Define Candidate System Architecture&lt;/a>, and the same cross-functional team can be
    used, augmented as necessary with specific skills and knowledge relating to the domains of the emerging subsystems.
&lt;/p></howtoStaff>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription>
</xmi:XMI>
